document_data.mainbody:
Ababuio was a god of luck worshiped on the island nation of Wa. They were one of the Eight Million Gods.
One of the mortal descendants of Ababuio in the mid&ndash14 century DR was believed to be Osari Daizan, the daimyo of the prosperous province of Tifuido on the island of Tsukishima. In reverence to Ababuio, he carefully observed a longstanding tradition among the Osari clan of fishing for jellyfish daily, going out to the beach each dawn with a net.
